HEADWORD: Fabaceae
<hw>Fabaceae</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A large natural family of
trees, shrubs, vines, and herbs bearing bean pods; divided for
convenience into the subfamilies <fam>Caesalpiniacea</fam>;
<fam>Mimosaceae</fam>; <fam>Papilionaceae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Leguminosae, family <fam>Leguminosae</fam>, family
<fam>Fabaceae</fam>, legume family, pea family.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fabaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
